http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/Four-held-for-bid-to-smuggle-ganja-into-prison/article14463131.ece

 The Puzhal Police on Saturday apprehended four persons who allegedly attempted to smuggle ganja into the Puzhal Central Prison. Sivabalan, Inspector of Police, Puzhal, and other police personnel were conducting checks on vehicles near Kathirvedu on Friday. They intercepted four youth in two motorcycles and since they gave contradictory replies, the police frisked them and also checked their bags. The team recovered four cellphones and 300 grams of ganja from their possession.During interrogation, the youth confessed that the substance was to be supplied to a few murder suspects who were lodged in the prison. The police arrested the youth and remanded to judicial custody.